50|$|Multiple <b>corporal</b> <b>punishments</b> were {{implemented}} by the Qin, such as death by boiling, chariots, beating, and permanent mutilation {{in the form of}} tattooing and castration. People who committed crimes were also sentenced to hard labor for the state.|$|R
